The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Cricketer dies

London: A 44-year-old cricketer has died after being hit in the chest by the ball at a village match in Porthleven, Cornwall. 

Ambulance-man Derek Newman was representing Porthleven Cricket Club against local rivals St Just when the incident took place on Sunday. 

He was treated by fellow paramedics on the pitch before being taken to the hospital, where he later died. 

Porthleven Cricket Clubs chairman John Walker said: He went for a high catch, it hit him in the chest and he collapsed. (PTI) 




